article.headline: Portland 78, San Francisco 60
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Reserve guard Jared Stohl set a school record with nine 3-pointers and finished with a career-high 33 points in Portland's 78-60 win over San Francisco on Thursday. The 6-foot-1 guard took only one shot from inside the arc and missed that. But he hit all six of his free throws. Nik Raivio added 17 points for the Pilots (9-7, 1-1 West Coast Conference). Dior Lowhorn led San Francisco (8-10, 0-3) with 22 points. Portland trailed only once, 4-3. Stohl and backcourt mate T.J. Campbell quickly got hot from long range, and the Pilots built a 45-26 halftime lead. Stohl connected on a pair of 3s early in the second half to help Portland push its lead to 53-30. The Pilots finished with a team-record 14 3-pointers.
